First Read: 10-Feb-26
SB288 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to agriculture authorities; to amend Sections
5 11-20-71, 11-20-73, and 11-20-81, as last amended by Act
6 2025-301, 2025 Regular Session, Code of Alabama 1975; to
7 provide the board of directors to appoint a successor for each
8 director on the board; to allow an agriculture authority to
9 purchase goods or services through a national or regional
10 governmental cooperative purchasing program; to provide that
11 tax proceeds from the sale of alcoholic beverages collected by
12 an agriculture authority are rebated to the agriculture
13 authority; and to make nonsubstantive, technical revisions to
14 update existing code language to current style.
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
16 Section 1. Sections 11-20-71, 11-20-73, and 11-20-81,
17 as last amended by Act 2025-301, 2025 Regular Session, Code of
18 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
19 "§11-20-71
20 (a)(1) The board of directors of an agriculture
21 authority shall be as specified in the articles and in
22 accordance with Section 11-20-70.
23 (2) When a director vacates his or her office prior to
24 the expiration of his or her term, the board of directors of
25 an agriculture authority incorporated prior to January 1,
26 2022, shall appoint a successor to serve the remainder of the
27 director's term.
28 (b) Each agriculture authority shall have a chair, vice
Page 1

(b) Each agriculture authority shall have a chair, vice
SB288 Enrolled
29 chair, secretary, and treasurer to be elected by the board of
30 directors. The offices of secretary and treasurer may be held
31 by the same personindividual. A majority of the directors
32 shall constitute a quorum for the transaction of business. The
33 officers and directors shall serve for the terms provided for
34 in the articles. A director may not draw any salary for any
35 service rendered or for any duty performed as director. The
36 duties of the chair, vice chair, secretary, and treasurer
37 shall be those as are customarily performed by these officers
38 and as may be prescribed by the board of directors.
39 (c) All directors shall serve until their successors
40 are appointed or until they cease to be qualified. Vacancies
41 on the board shall be filled as provided for in the articles,
42 but any individual appointed to fill a vacancy shall serve
43 only for the unexpired portion of the term. In the event any
44 uncertainty arises as to the terms of office of the directors,
45 the county commission or individual authorized to appoint the
46 directors may clarify the term by adoption of an appropriate
47 resolution or by execution of an appropriate certificate, and
48 the term of office shall be as so clarified.
49 (d) All proceedings of the board of directors of an
50 agriculture authority shall be reduced to writing by the
51 secretary of the authority and shall be signed by at least two
52 directors present at the proceedings. Copies of the
53 proceedings, when certified by the secretary under the seal of
54 the agriculture authority, shall be received in all courts as
55 prima facie evidence of the matters and things therein
56 certified.
Page 2

certified.
SB288 Enrolled
57 (e) Directors of an agriculture authority must be
58 residents and qualified electors of the county within the
59 authorized operational area of the authority. If any director
60 ceases to be a resident of the county, he or she shall cease
61 to be a director, and the position shall remain vacant until a
62 successor is appointed in accordance with the articles and
63 this article.
64 (f) A director of an agriculture authority may not have
65 an interest, directly or indirectly, in any contract of work,
66 material, or services, or the profits therefrom, to be
67 furnished or performed for the authority under this article if
68 the director has, directly or indirectly, more than a 10
69 percent interest in any business, firm, or corporation, or
70 profits thereof, furnishing or providing work, materials, or
71 services.
72 (g) The board of directors may appoint former members
73 of the board to serve as directors emeritus. Directors
74 emeritus shall not have voting rights on the board or
75 otherwise directly participate in meetings of the board.
76 Directors emeritus shall receive no compensation for their
77 service, but may be granted benefits and may attend events of
78 the authority as guests of the authority at the discretion of
79 the board. The directors emeritus shall serve as goodwill
80 ambassadors for the authority and may perform duties at the
81 request of the authority. Directors emeritus shall be subject
82 to subsections (e) and (f)."
