382 "§11-20-81
383 (a) An agriculture authority, as a governmental entity,
384 is exempt from the payment of all state, county, and municipal
385 sales and use taxes. An agriculture authority and its
386 contractors shall be granted a certificate of exemption from
387 sales and use taxes by the Department of Revenue as provided
388 in Sections 40-9-14.1 and 40-9-60, or other general law.
389 (b)(1) Any county or municipal sales and use tax
390 proceeds and any county or municipal tax proceeds from the
391 sale of alcoholic beverages that are collected by an
392 agriculture authority; a joint venture of the authority,
Page 14

agriculture authority; a joint venture of the authority,
SB288 Enrolled
393 including a public/private venture of the authority; or a
394 lessee or sublessee of the authority or a joint venture of the
395 authority, and remitted to a local taxing authority shall be
396 rebated by that local taxing authority to the agriculture
397 authority.
398 (2) For an agriculture authority established pursuant
399 to this article, after May 1, 2022, the county commission, at
400 the time of the formation of the authority, may opt-outopt out
401 of the requirement to rebate sales taxes collected by a
402 private entity, joint venture partner, or public-private
403 partnership.
404 (c) An agriculture authority is exempt from paying all
405 state, county, and local ad valorem taxes.
406 (d) An agriculture authority is exempt from paying any
407 other taxes levied by a county, municipality, or other
408 political subdivision of the state, including, but not limited
409 to, license and excise taxes imposed relating to the privilege
410 of engaging in any activities that the authority may engage
411 in.
412 (e) All state and local lodging taxes collected by an
413 agriculture authority or by another entity operating a lodging
414 accommodation located on property owned by, leased from,
415 subleased from, or otherwise made available by an agriculture
416 authority and remitted to the state or local taxing authority
417 shall be rebated by that taxing authority to the agriculture
418 authority."
419 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
420 1, 2026.
